            ],
            summary: None,
            summary_detail: None,
            content: [
                Content {
                    value: "<a href=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiLgLwBxPxv4QLLFEYu5ZDwLKHbwilIHQftiP0JulWizQCu0XVGemWKZ4juZlQx-KzFX-K9H9wy3hmSzGz04mG3acWochqFTU3kD2c6ok65oWFBdnd9PRSOcp6klPMjqUbJBDYyY6EQvi0Ah8Be3j1BwSfQ5DLry3R3c9N52Tk4OKoSpOZkq_nVmp_wYRNP/s2546/PageViews-010126.png\"style=\"clear: right; display: block; float: right; padding: 1em 0px; text-align: center;\"><img alt=\"\"border=\"0\"data-original-height=\"716\"data-original-width=\"2546\"src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiLgLwBxPxv4QLLFEYu5ZDwLKHbwilIHQftiP0JulWizQCu0XVGemWKZ4juZlQx-KzFX-K9H9wy3hmSzGz04mG3acWochqFTU3kD2c6ok65oWFBdnd9PRSOcp6klPMjqUbJBDYyY6EQvi0Ah8Be3j1BwSfQ5DLry3R3c9N52Tk4OKoSpOZkq_nVmp_wYRNP/s200/PageViews-010126.png\"width=\"200\"/></a>This is the one thousandth post to this blog in the 212 months since the<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2007/04/mass-market-scholarly-communication.html\">first post</a>. That is an average of 4.7 posts per month, or just over one per week, which is my long-term goal for the roughly half my time that isn't taken up with grand-parenting.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhCbL1NiUi4sa7g1F3KcJH4mBsRnFXTYi30j9wLBFFllpOkhlwH26ikzGjAqMOntafET2B8gzlyE7Z3gRb5n3IIXBUqok8mQtG-3UgVGydNrbLt_sGupLcs-PqfIuUyh-dqpmkZlqhIZBohxg0_SxEGB-r4O6g06MjECG4X4ExCqHWKg6ZSQDRC6uTnyqK0/s1962/PostViews-010126.png\"style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\"data-original-height=\"1412\"data-original-width=\"1962\"height=\"144\"src=\"https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhCbL1NiUi4sa7g1F3KcJH4mBsRnFXTYi30j9wLBFFllpOkhlwH26ikzGjAqMOntafET2B8gzlyE7Z3gRb5n3IIXBUqok8mQtG-3UgVGydNrbLt_sGupLcs-PqfIuUyh-dqpmkZlqhIZBohxg0_SxEGB-r4O6g06MjECG4X4ExCqHWKg6ZSQDRC6uTnyqK0/w200-h144/PostViews-010126.png\"width=\"200\"/></a>Some posts are a lot of work, and take more than a week. Major talks, such as<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2025/09/the-gaslit-asset-class.html\"><i>The Gaslit Asset Class</i></a>or<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2025/04/paul-evan-peters-award-lecture.html\"><i>Lessons from LOCKSS</i></a>typically represent a month's work, as do long posts such as<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2025/12/sabotaging-bitcoin.html\"><i>Sabotaging Biitcoin</i></a>,<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2024/12/drones.html\"><i>Drones</i></a>or<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2025/05/the-dawn-of-nvidias-technology.html\"><i>The Dawn Of Nvidia's Technology</i></a>.<br /><br />The 1000 posts have gained over 6.88M page views, 7.6% of which were for my<a href=\"https://blog.dshr.org/2022/02/ee380-talk.html\"><i>EE380 Talk</i></a>. Less publicized but popular posts get around 30K page views, well above the 6.9K average.<br /><br />The only one of these statistics that I care about is the goal of a post a week. Having an audience is nice when it happens, but that's not why I'm writing. I write for myself, to understand not necessarily to communicate. Despite this, I'd like to thank those who read and comment.<br /><br />",
                    content_type: Some(
                        MimeType(
                            "html",
                        ),
                    ),
                    language: None,
                    base: None,
                },
            ],
            published: Some(
